The paper deals with a jamming-resistant receiver scheme for a massive MIMO uplink system. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information. The paper also involves network security and communication, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper discusses jamming attacks, which is a type of cyber-attack, and hence, it can also be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of linear receive filters, which is a signal processing technique, and hence, it can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the optimization of the receiver and power allocation, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
